title: $:/plugins/rimir/cascade-palette/changelog
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

! Changelog

|!Version |!Date |!Changes |
|0.0.17 |2026-05-20 |''Number kind + slider.'' New ''`ca-kind: number`'' renders a numeric row with an inline horizontal slider bar (when both `ca-min` and `ca-max` are set) and the current value. ''`+`'' / ''`-`'' adjust by `ca-step` (default 1); ''Shift'' uses `ca-step-medium` (default 5); ''Ctrl'' uses `ca-step-large` (default 20). Keys are matched on `e.code` (`Equal`, `NumpadAdd`, `Minus`, `NumpadSubtract`) for layout-portability. Value clamps to [`ca-min`, `ca-max`] on write. Enter closes the palette; Shift-Enter keeps it open. First shipped: ''Max results per stage'' (bound to `$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/max-results`, range 5–100, default 30). |
|0.0.16 |2026-05-20 |''Toggle kind + Settings entry.'' New ''`ca-kind: toggle`'' renders a checkbox row bound to a tiddler/field/JSON-path via scribe-style fields (`ca-bind-tiddler`, `ca-bind-field`, `ca-bind-path`, `ca-true-value`, `ca-false-value`). ''Space'' flips the value inline without closing the palette; Enter flips + closes; Shift-Enter flips + stays. New root entry ''Settings'' drills into all tiddlers tagged ''`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/setting`'' — auto-clustered by contributing plugin so any plugin can ship its own settings without needing a sub-stage. First shipped setting: ''Grouping'' (`$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/grouping-enabled`), live-toggleable from the palette. When grouping is off, the engine keeps items in their natural sort and suppresses headers globally. |
|0.0.15 |2026-05-20 |''Visual grouping in result list.'' Items now cluster by contributing plugin: the engine derives a group label from `$tw.wiki.getShadowSource(title)` → plugin tiddler's `name` field, so contributors don't need any prefix convention. New optional ''`ca-group`'' field overrides the auto-derived label (use to cross-cluster items from several plugins under a shared header, e.g. "Mutations"). Cluster ordering follows the lowest `ca-order` member of each cluster. Headers are ''suppressed when a stage has only one cluster'' — single-plugin action menus still render as flat lists. Applies in both root and drilled stages. `stage.results` is reordered into visual sequence so keyboard arrows still index linearly through visible rows. |
|0.0.14 |2026-05-19 |''Removed appify-specific entries from the engine.'' The ''Switch Apps'' and ''Return to Wiki'' entries previously shipped here were appify-specific contributions and have moved into `rimir/appify` 0.2.29 (under `palette/`). The engine stays domain-agnostic. Catalogue plugins (orga-palette, appify itself, future others) ship entries; the engine just discovers them via the standard tags. |
|0.0.13 |2026-05-19 |''Stale-stage fix.'' When popping a stage (via Esc, Shift-Tab, or breadcrumb click), the now-top stage is recomputed so any state that changed while in deeper stages is reflected. Example: open palette in default wiki → Switch Apps → Shift-Enter on orga app (palette stays, app activates) → Esc back to root → Current App entry now appears (visibility filter re-evaluates). |
|0.0.12 |2026-05-19 |''Shift-Enter / Shift-Click fires the action without closing the palette.'' After the action runs, the current stage is recomputed so any field mutations are reflected immediately. Useful for batch ops like "Mark Done on these three tasks" or "Switch sections to compare views" without re-opening the palette each time. Drill items ignore the modifier (drilling doesn't close anyway). Key-hint footer updated. |
|0.0.11 |2026-05-19 |Three changes: (a) ''Critical fix:'' `findActionParent` now prefers the `statewrap` widget over the appify-app widget. `$action-statewrap-navigate` walks `parentWidget` UP looking for the widget whose `statewrapContext` is set — and that's the `statewrap` widget itself (a descendant of appify-app, not appify-app). Parenting actions to appify-app meant walking up from there and never visiting statewrap. Symptom: Enter on entries in appify mode did nothing visible (navigate action ran but found no statewrap). Now resolved — statewrap navigation works in appify. (b) New engine field ''`ca-visibility-filter`'' on entries: if present and the filter returns empty, the entry is hidden from the root menu. Used by catalogues to gate entries on the active app. (c) Two new demo entries: ''Switch Apps'' (drill to list `$:/tags/rimir/appify/app` tiddlers; picking sets `$:/state/rimir/appify/active-app`) and ''Return to Wiki'' (leaf, visible only when an app is active, clears the active-app state). |
|0.0.10 |2026-05-19 |''Shift-Tab acts as back-out'' (same as Esc — pops one stage, closes palette at root). Mentioned as optional in the original keyboard model but wasn't wired; now it is. Key-hint footer updated. |
|0.0.9 |2026-05-19 |Three improvements: (a) action-parent resolution now prefers `appify-app` widget over plain navigator. The action widget inherits appify-app's variable scope (statewrap channels, instance ID) so `$action-statewrap-navigate` and friends actually work inside appify. Falls back to navigator, then rootWidget. Method renamed from `findNavigator` to `findActionParent`. (b) Items returned by a stage's `ca-next-scope` are now inspected for a `ca-kind` field — if present, they're treated as cascade-aware entries (drill or leaf) rather than plain dynamic items. Enables hierarchical "entry group" patterns like `Orga types → 12 entity-type entries → drill into each`. (c) Dynamic item rows now render with a right-aligned dimmed title column (raw tiddler title) and prefer the `caption` field for the left-aligned display name. Title truncates with ellipsis and shows the full title on hover. |
|0.0.8 |2026-05-19 |Two fixes uncovered after the 0.0.7 startup-module mount: (a) navigator-routed actions (`<$action-navigate>`, `tm-edit-tiddler`, etc.) silently failed because the widget now lives in document.body — outside the navigator's widget subtree. New `invokeViaNavigator` helper finds the navigator widget under `$tw.pageWidgetNode` at action-fire time and invokes the action wikitext with the navigator as parentWidget so events bubble naturally into its handlers. Falls back to `$tw.rootWidget` if no navigator found (so global messages like `tm-save-wiki` still work). (b) Selected row now calls `scrollIntoView({block: "nearest"})` so it stays visible when navigating past the viewport bounds. |
|0.0.7 |2026-05-19 |Mount moved from `$:/tags/AboveStory` (tiddler-based) to a startup module that injects the widget directly into `document.body`. Reason: `AboveStory` doesn't render inside appify's substituted UI, so the palette silently failed in app mode. Startup-module mount is independent of any template tag — the widget DOM is always present regardless of which UI mode is active. Mount tiddler (`mount.tid`) deleted; new file `widgets/cascade-palette-startup.js`. |
|0.0.6 |2026-05-19 |UI visibility fix — replaced fragile `<<colour ...>>` macros with hardcoded colors (light baseline + `prefers-color-scheme: dark` override). Selected row now has a blue background, white text, and a darker left-border accent so the highlight is obvious regardless of theme. Earlier symptom: popup looked greyed-out except for the input field, and selected rows only changed text color. |
|0.0.5 |2026-05-19 |Default hotkey reverted to ''Ctrl-Space'' — works correctly once the trailing-newline fix (0.0.4) is in place. The earlier "Ctrl-Space doesn't reach TW" symptom was actually the trailing-newline parse failure all along. |
|0.0.4 |2026-05-19 |Shortcut-key tiddler trailing newline fix — the shipped `$:/config/shortcuts/rimir-cascade-palette-open` was a `.tid` file ending in `\n`, so TW resolved `((rimir-cascade-palette-open))` to `"ctrl-space\n"` and the parser couldn't match the key. Rewrote without trailing newline and omitted `type` field per `feedback-tid-vs-txt-meta` (avoids `.txt`+`.meta` split on user edits). |
|0.0.3 |2026-05-19 |Mount tag fixed (`$:/tags/AboveStory` instead of `$:/tags/PageTemplate` — wrong tag prevented the widget from rendering). Default hotkey changed from `ctrl-space` to `alt+p` — Ctrl-Space reaches Chrome JS but TW's keyboard manager doesn't match it on some Windows / WSL Chrome setups. Diagnostic console logs at widget mount + hotkey-listener registration + message receipt; harmless in production. Settings + readme document the rebind path. |
|0.0.2 |2026-05-19 |''Engine v0.1.'' Cascade widget with stage stack, Tab/Esc/Enter keyboard model, entry discovery via `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/entry`, action discovery via `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/action` filtered by `ca-entity-type` (plus globals via `ca-entity-type: *`), filter substitution variables `<<query>>` / `<<picked>>` / `<<parent-picked>>` / `<<stage-N-picked>>`, 3-tier default-action resolution (stage default → entity default → navigate fallback), breadcrumb with click-to-jump-back, four demo entries (Control Panel, Save Wiki, Advanced Search, Recent Tiddlers…). Doc tabs still scaffold-level — full protocol doc lands in 0.0.4. |
|0.0.1 |2026-05-19 |''Initial scaffold.'' Plugin skeleton — readme, documentation, settings, changelog, license, icon, doc-template overview. No widget yet. |
